<body><div class=WordSection1>
<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>🤖 AI001 Week 3 — English Worksheet</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> Context and Examples · <strong>Course:</strong> AI Coding with Replit Agent · <strong>Time:</strong> about 45 minutes</p>
<p>This week you make your prompts smarter by adding <strong>context</strong> (who you are, what you like, who it is for) and <strong>examples</strong> ("make it like this site"). You also use <strong>negative constraints</strong> — telling the AI what <em>not</em> to do.</p>
<hr />
<h2>1 · Predict 🔮</h2>
<p>Read each prompt. Before the AI builds it, write how the extra information will change the result.</p>
<pre><code>Build a gallery site that shows cat photos.
</code></pre>
<p><strong>This works, but the AI knows nothing about you. What might it guess wrong?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code>I'm 12 and I love cats. Build a gallery of cat photos,
Pinterest-style cards, with cute warm colors.
</code></pre>
<p><strong>The context and example were added. How will this result be different from the first?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code>Build a study site for me. Don't use complicated words,
and don't make the buttons tiny.
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Two "don't" rules were added. Why might telling the AI what NOT to do help?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>2 · Spot the Weak Prompt 🐛</h2>
<p>Each prompt below is missing context, an example, or a needed "don't" rule. Read what the student <strong>wanted</strong>, then rewrite it to add what is missing.</p>
<p><strong>Prompt A</strong> — The student is <strong>11</strong> and wants their <strong>first</strong> project: a simple page about <strong>soccer</strong>, easy to understand.</p>
<pre><code>Make a soccer page.
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Hint:</strong> add who you are ("I'm 11, this is my first project") and a "keep it simple" rule.</p>
<p><strong>Write a stronger prompt:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>What context or constraint did you add?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Prompt B</strong> — The student wants their page to <strong>look like the Naver homepage</strong> layout.</p>
<pre><code>Make a homepage with news on it.
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Hint:</strong> give an example: "make the layout like the Naver homepage".</p>
<p><strong>Write a stronger prompt:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>What example did you give?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Prompt C</strong> — The student keeps getting <strong>dark colors</strong> and <strong>hard words</strong>, but they want <strong>bright colors</strong> and <strong>simple words</strong>.</p>
<pre><code>Make a fun page about space.
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Hint:</strong> add the example feel you want ("bright, cartoon-style") and the "don't" rules.</p>
<p><strong>Write a stronger prompt:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>What did you add?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>3 · A Site About Something You Love 📸</h2>
<p>Pick a topic you really like. Write <strong>one prompt</strong> that includes all three:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>context</strong> — who you are or who the site is for,</li>
<li><strong>an example</strong> — at least one site or style to copy ("like ___"),</li>
<li><strong>a constraint</strong> — at least one "don't" rule.</li>
</ul>
<p>Run it in Replit. Send a <strong>photo or video</strong> of the result, then explain what you did. Use these sentence starters — write 4 to 6 sentences total.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>My topic was …</p>
<p>The context I gave the AI was …</p>
<p>The example I used was "make it like …"</p>
<p>The "don't" rule I added was …</p>
<p>Adding context changed the result by …</p>
<p>If I had more time, I would …</p>
</blockquote>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>4 · Save Your Best Prompt 🗒️</h2>
<p>Write the full prompt you used in part 3, word for word. Underline the <strong>context</strong>, circle the <strong>example</strong>, and box the <strong>"don't" rule</strong> so you can see all three parts.</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h3>Submit ✅</h3>
<p>Send this worksheet + a photo (or video) of your site + the prompt you used to teacher on KakaoTalk.</p>
<div class="footer">영어코딩 · <b>english-coding.co.uk</b></div>
</div></body></html>
